description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Deputy Team Manager&lt;/span&gt; - &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;New Horizons, Slough&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are very excited to offer the opportunity for a new role within the Slough Community Mental Health Team – an experienced clinician to take on the Deputy Team Lead post and be part of the leadership team within the Slough.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Job&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the operational and strategic developments of the service.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead on the formation of a small duty team to a Short Term Intervention Service within Slough Care Pathways.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with CRHTT, Children and Families and the Thames Valley Police.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be responsible for the safe management of the service and to ensure referrals are triaged and discharged appropriately.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with senior clinicians in the development and implementation of care packages/ risk assessment and management for users with severe and enduring mental illnesses.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Some of the benefits of joining our team:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;AfC Salary ranging from £40,681 - £46,294 per annum inclusive of High Cost Area Supplement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working opportunities and a strong emphasis on your work, life balance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Annual leave – 27 days for new starters, plus bank holidays. Increasing to 29 days after 5 years and 33 days after 10 years NHS service. Pro rata for part time staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent learning and development opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary sacrifice scheme for a new car&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous maternity, paternity and adoption leave for eligible staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced IT enablement and support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confidential telephone care service providing independent support and advice for staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;And so much more&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The “must haves” for you to be considered for this role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Registered Mental Health Nurse/ or Approved Social Worker/ Occupational Therapist&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evidence of continuous professional development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience working in a CMHT&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you recognise yourself in these requirements, we would recommend you apply today!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are happy to answer any questions that you may have. Please don’t hesitate to call Alan Buckley on 01753 690950 or email: Alan.Buckley@berkshire.nhs.uk who’ll be delighted to help.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
